make a workspace folder: $ mkdir workspace

Start rails project: rails new project_name

adding database: (default) Gemfile

Install bundle: bundle install

Running the rails server on a local machine
$ cd ~/workspace/hello_app/
$ rails server

{
Running the rails server on a cloud IDE
$ cd ~/workspace/hello_app/
$ rails server -b $IP -p $PORT
}

create repository:
1. git init
2. git add -A
3. git commit -m "first commit"
4. (git remote add origin https://github.com/markemil/hello_app.git)
5. git push -u origin master

start coding

git add -A
git commit -m "Comment"
git push origin master

git log
git status

Scaffold:
rails generate scaffold User name:string email:string

Migrate for db:
rake db:migrate
